Godwin Isenyo, Kaduna TROOPS have reportedly killed five bandits terrorising the Anaba general area of Igabi Local Government of Kaduna State. A government statement titled, ‘Troops neutralise five bandits, rescue nine citizens’, disclosed this on Tuesday. According to the Commissioner for Internal Security and Home Affairs, Mr. Samuel Aruwan, a military operation’s update submitted to the Kaduna State Government reported that troops rescued nine kidnapped citizens from the armed bandits in separate locations of crossing points. Aruwan said several bandits also escaped with bullet wounds into Malum Forest in the ongoing onslaught against the criminals that blocked Kwanar Tsintsiya axis of Kaduna-Zaria in Igabi Local Government Area. He added that five of the rescued nine, in the early hours of Tuesday, during debriefing, explained how the bandits burnt the corpses of four of their fellow criminals. The nine rescued persons, he said, had since been handed over to their families. According to him, Governor Nasir El-Rufai commended the troops for their resilience and bravery. Copyright PUNCH.
